<h2>What is precision medicine?
</h2>
<p>In precision medicine, physicians consider an individual’s specific genes, medical history, environment, and lifestyle.  They use these factors – along with the specific characteristics of the  patient's tumor – to balance various options for  treatment and prevention of diseases, including breast cancer. This state-of-the-art approach reduces the chances of over-treating or under-treating breast cancer by tailoring treatment to each patient’s precise needs based on the characteristics of the tumor.
</p>
