   <h2>What role do genes play in cancer treatment?</h2>
   <p>Genes make up the code that a cell uses to carry out all its functions. The cell’s machinery uses this code to make the proteins that perform specific roles in the cell. Cancer arises when some genes are mutated at their nucleotide sequence, resulting in protein malfunction. Physicians can test cancer cells from a tissue sample to discover which genes are abnormal. The physician can then use knowledge about the abnormal genes to recommend treatments personalized to the patient.
</p>
